<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="E" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Ebb1" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Ebb,</orth> subst. the reflux of the tide: <bibl n="shak. tmp 5.270" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. V, 270</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.4.125" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 4, 125</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.455" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 455</bibl>. <cit><quote>mine eyes, never since at e.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.435" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 435</bibl></cit>. Figuratively, == decline, decay: <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.42" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 42</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.8.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 8, 56</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 2.2.150" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. II, 2, 150</bibl>. <emph>Ebb</emph> and <emph>flow</emph> an image of capriciousness: <cit><quote>his pettish lines, his --s, his flows,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.139" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 3, 139</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>